docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 17. -- The return to this country on its long-term investments abroad during 1933 exceeded by $49,000,000 the sums paid to foreigners on account of their investments here, according to an analysis of the international long-term capital movement to and from the United States by Amos E. Taylor of the Commerce Department's Finance and Investment Division.
